    "long_instructions": "# Do This:\r\n1. Add 4 new variables, one for each type: \r\n    - **String** (text)\r\n    - **Integer** (whole number)\r\n    - **Boolean** (`True` or `False`)\r\n    - **Float** (decimal number)\r\n2. Modify the `print` statements so that they print out each variable.\r\n\t- *Hint: What do you need to add to your code when printing out a string?*\r\n\r\n--- \r\n###AI Tutor Support\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure how to define variables?**]\r\nAsk AI: \r\n- How do I create a variable for a number in Python?\r\n- How do I store `True` or `False` in a variable?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**Stuck on printing?**]\r\nAsk AI:\r\n- Why do I get an error when I try to print a number with text?\r\n- How do I fix a TypeError when printing different types together?\r\n:::\r\n",
